<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-29T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="631" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/625a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-29T19:00:00-04:00">August 29, 1934—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>115. Please inform Brazilian Government that the Department intends to
                            give public notice shortly of this Government’s intention to negotiate a
                            Reciprocal Foreign Trade Agreement with the Government of Brazil.<note n="13" xml:id="d631fn13">For text of public notice and statistics
                                concerning trade between the United States and Brazil, issued by the
                                Department of State on August 31, 1934, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>, September 1, 1934, pp.
                                144–149, <hi rend="italic">passim.</hi></note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>